topics.body:
We'll I'm back at college now, and I'm all set for tomorrow when spring classes start up!
This semester, as far as I can tell, is going to be awesome. The earliest time I need to be at any of my classes is about 10:30 AM, and I'm taking about another five classes. I've got what possibly my final Math class I'll ever have to take in my lifetime, another English class, another Religion classes for my Religious Studies major, and TWO ASTRONOMY CLASSES.

Okay, one's a normal class and the other's the lab for the same class, but as a astronomy and spaceflight lover, I AM GOING TO HAVE A BLAST. Especially if anyone is remotely aware of all the cool stuff that's going to happen this year.

_Remember Pluto, anyone?_ New Horizons is going to make its epic flyby past it this summer, and we're going to get not only a sh*t-ton load of awesome data from it and its many moons, but WE'RE FINALLY GOING TO HAVE HD REAL-LIFE PICTURES OF PLUTO, UP CLOSE (sort of)!!!
_I've been tracking the New Horizons mission ever since it launched in 2006, and I am super excited for this tremendous even to occur. And my parents were not kidding that I was going to be in college when this happens. Has it almost been that long already?_
_My life is indeed awesome. :D_

~...Oh, and then there's the Dawn spacecraft that's going to go visit the formerly-largest asteroid, and the only dwarf planet in the asteroid belt, Ceres, but I don't think people are going to be that excited or interested as much...unless I'm proven wrong about that fact...~

2015 is going to be one kickass year. 
Wish me luck everyone.
